  "text": "The values of this P/Al atomic ratio for the 23 beads that give a diffractogram compatible with variscite are diverse and vary between a little less than the unit and a little less than six. Despite the fact that accepted values for Iberian variscite are around 0.8-1.8, values above 2 indicate the presence of abnormally-high quantities of Fe or Ca. In the case of the Fe, it would appear to be substituting the Al, leading to strengite [FePO 4 ·2H 2 O] as a minor crystalline phase. We are not able to detect this phase from the diffractograms, so it is unlikely that our samples contain strengite [CITATION_1] .",
